social_posts.post_text:
I feel like every mother to be should read up a little on the NICU. Not to scare you, simply to have some knowledge of it. Most parents wish they had. And, before you say, “that won’t happen to me.” Remember, the day before we had our preemies, it didn’t happen to us either…
One year ago today, December 29th, 2021, I never would have thought this could have happened to me. I was 24 weeks pregnant with the twins, thinking “how am I going to make it 4 more months?” I thought for sure I delivery around 37 weeks without a doubt. Never did it cross my mind would I go into labor early…4 months early. No one ever educated me on preterm labor and I knew absolutely nothing about the NICU. I never realized it was an ICU for babies. How would I even know this stuff? Not many mamas do. I want to try and help educate as many mamas as I can about preterm labor and the NICU, because I went into both blindsided and let me tell you, it’s absolutely terrifying. Watching your babies fight for their lives when there is nothing you can do to protect them is traumatizing. I wish I knew what preterm labor was and maybe, just maybe, I could have prevented delivering my twins at only 24 weeks. I know God has a plan for me and my story, hopefully it’s to help other mamas be aware of what preterm labor signs can be or what life in the NICU is like. I want to help. I want to make a difference. I am finally ready to share my story. To help other Mamas. If there was a way I could prevent any mama from seeing their baby in the NICU, I would. It’s the most painful experience in the world to leave the hospital without your baby in your arms. To watch your baby go through what they go through in the NICU is unbearable. No mama should have to go through it. Whether I can help one mama or 1 million, I want to make a difference. I want to be an advocate for Mamas out there.  So before you think, “that would never happen to me”, it wasn’t going to happen to me either.  #nicu #nicumom #pregnancy #parenting #kids #baby #preemie #mama #twins

social_posts.post_text: Ace, one year ago, our lives quickly changed forever. You’ve gone through the unimaginable. Watching you grow and develop outside the womb was a wild and emotional ride. No baby should have to start their lives out the way you did. They told me you only had a 40% chance or less of survival before my c-section and a way smaller chance of being healthy. You defied the odds. Alive and Healthy. and 20 times your birthday weight haha 👏🏼 Happy FIRST Birthday Ace 🎉  #happybirthday #one #firstbirthday #preemie #nicu #24weeksold #miracle #godisgood

Aspen, your FIRST trip around the sun. You spent your first four months in the NICU. Your chance of survival was low. You had emergency heart surgery at only 13 days old, weighing only 810 grams 💕 You had the largest hole in your heart Vanderbilt has ever seen. You are so strong! It’s been a crazy year. You’re a wild little girl now. Happy First Birthday Aspen 🫶  #happybirthday #one #aspen #preemie #24weeks #miracle #nicu #nicubaby

Happy Birthday to our Miracle babies. We love you so much! This year has been full of mountains and valleys and we are back climbing. I am so proud of how these two have fought from the moment they came into this world. You were given less than 50% chance to live and we are a year in with a lot to go. We have met some of the most amazing nurses and doctors on this planet and we are forever grateful for them. Finally, the strength my wife showed in her darkest time is something that I will be forever grateful for. Her calm presence in the midst of the chaos is what kept these two beautiful children alive to let them fight on their own. This is the most overlooked part of it all. WE ALL love you to the moon and back honey!!! @jdormady_
